  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this fMRI study is to investigate neural indices of relapse in cannabis
      dependence. The development and maintenance of drug addictions have been associated with
      deficits in cognitive control, craving and impaired stress regulation. Therefore, neural
      markers of brain processes underlying the beforementioned components will be studied.
      Subsequent follow-up drug use interviews will reveal associations between relapse in cannabis
      dependence and alterations in brain networks of cognitive control, craving and stress.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
